						               													<description>Harz IV is a freebee add-on to the game Igels. It was distributed during the Spiel 2006 and was also included in the magazine Games Orbit, printed by Pegasus Games.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The card is a reference to the social/unemployment benefit &amp;quot;Hartz IV&amp;quot; granted in Germany. Also, it is a word-play as the German word &amp;quot;Harz&amp;quot; means &amp;quot;resin&amp;quot; and this is were the card comes into play. Here is the card's text:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Wer einmal in die Harzfalle tappt, kommt kaum noch vom Fleck. Harz klebt sofort vier beliebige Gegner zusammen, die in dieser Runde nicht mehr weiter gespielt werden k&amp;ouml;nnen.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This translates roughly into:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Whoever falls just once into the resin(Harz)-trap makes hardly any headway. Harz immediately sticks together any four enemies, who cannot be played any further this turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The two cards Harz IV cards you get are simply shuffled into your standard card deck. They are of the &amp;quot;Unterst&amp;uuml;tzungskarten&amp;quot; (support cards) type and can be played as any support card can in the support phase of any combat.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
